Attributes.WarningText: <F1> Start Control changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Controls the tools that are started using the <F1> key or equivalent IPMI command. [Tool Suite] starts a graphical suite of tools which support System Information, UEFI setup, Platform Update, Raid Setup, OS installation and Diagnostics functions. [Text Setup] starts a text mode UEFI setup utility. [Auto] starts text mode UEFI setup if Serial Over Lan (SOL) or "Console Redirection" are enabled or SOL is configured to [Auto] and an active session is detected. Attributes.WarningText: Active Video changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: This setting only applies if the server has an add-in video adapter. When the option ROM is set to Legacy for both onboard and add-in video adapters, the Active Video setting controls which single adapter will display the System Setup utility. Regardless of this setting, the system boot early video is displayed at the onboard video only, and the management controller remote console shows the onboard video only. This setting does not affect how the OS chooses to display its graphical desktop.

Attributes.WarningText: Console Redirection changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Set remote console redirection preference to enable or disable console redirection. While [Auto] is selected, console redirection will be enabled automatically if IPMI Serial over LAN status is active.

Attributes.WarningText: Serial Port Sharing changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable the system Baseboard Management Controller to allow access to the system serial port. If this option is set to [Enabled], the BMC will be allowed to control the serial communication port as requested by remote control commands. If sharing is [Disabled], the serial port will be assigned to the BMC unless the "Serial Port Access Mode" is set to [Disabled].

Attributes.WarningText: Serial Port Access Mode changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: This option allows you to control the access the system Baseboard Management Controller has over the system serial port. (a)Shared mode: By selecting [Shared], the serial port will be available for POST and operating system use; however the BMC will/can monitor the serial data for a takeover control sequence.  (b)Dedicated mode: By selecting [Dedicated], the BMC will have complete control of the serial port and POST and/or the operating system will not be able to use the serial port.  (c)Disable mode: By selecting [Disabled], the BMC will not have any access to the serial port.

Attributes.WarningText: SP Redirection changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: This option is only displayed while "Console Redirection", "COM Port 1" and "COM Port 2" set to [Enabled]. It allows you to choose which COM port to have the redirection.

Attributes.WarningText: Turbo Mode changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enabling turbo mode can boost the overall CPU performance when all CPU cores are not being fully utilized. A CPU core can run above its rated frequency for a short period of time when it is in turbo mode.  When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: CPU P-state Control changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Select the method used to control CPU P-states (performance states). [None] disables all P-states and the CPUs run at either their rated frequency or in turbo mode (if turbo is enabled). When [Legacy] is selected, the CPU P-states will be presented to the operating system (OS) and the OS power management (OSPM) will directly control which P-state is selected. With [Autonomous], the P-states are controlled fully by system hardware. No P-state support is required in the OS or VM. [Cooperative] is a combination of Legacy and Autonomous. The P-states are still controlled in hardware but the OS can provide hints to the hardware for P-state limits and the desired setting. When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: C-States changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: C-states reduce CPU idle power. When [Legacy] is selected, the operating system initiates the C-state transitions. For E5/E7 CPUs, ACPI C1/C2/C3 map to Intel C1/C3/C6. For 6500/7500 CPUs, ACPI C1/C3 map to Intel C1/C3 (ACPI C2 is not available). Some OS SW may defeat the ACPI mapping (e.g. intel_idle driver). When [Autonomous] is selected, HALT and C1 request get converted to C6 requests in hardware. When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: C1 Enhanced Mode changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enabling C1E (C1 enhanced) state can save power by halting CPU cores that are idle. Note, an operating system that supports C1E state must be installed to take advantage of this feature. Changing this setting takes effect after the next reboot. When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" and [Legacy]/[Disabled] in "C-States" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: Hyper-Threading changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable Hyper Threading (Software Method to Enable/Disable Logical Processor threads).

Attributes.WarningText: Trusted Execution Technology changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable Intel Trusted Execution Technology (Intel TXT).

Attributes.WarningText: Intel Virtualization Technology changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable the Virtualization Technology.

Attributes.WarningText: Hardware Prefetcher changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Lightly threaded applications and some benchmarks can benefit from having the hardware prefetcher enabled.

Attributes.WarningText: Adjacent Cache Prefetch changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Lightly threaded applications and some benchmarks can benefit from having the adjacent cache line prefetch enabled.

Attributes.WarningText: DCU Streamer Prefetcher changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Lightly threaded applications and some benchmarks can benefit from having the DCU streamer prefetcher enabled.

Attributes.WarningText: DCU IP Prefetcher changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: DCU IP prefetcher is typically best left enabled for most environments. Some environments may benefit from having it disabled (e.g. Java).

Attributes.WarningText: DCA changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: DCA capable I/O devices such as network controllers can place data directly into the CPU cache, which improves response times.

Attributes.WarningText: Energy Efficient Turbo changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: When energy efficient turbo is enabled, the CPU's optimal turbo frequency will be tuned dynamically based on CPU utilization. The power/performance bias setting also influences energy efficient turbo. When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" and [Enabled] in "Turbo Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: Uncore Frequency Scaling changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: When enabled, the CPU uncore will dynamically change speed based on the workload. All miscellaneous logic inside the CPU package is considered the uncore.

Attributes.WarningText: MONITOR/MWAIT changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: MONITOR/MWAIT instructions are used to engage C-states. Some operating systems will re-enable C-states even when they are disabled in setup. To prevent this, disable MONNITOR/MWAIT. Please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" and [Disabled] in "C-States" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: PCIe ACSCTL changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable/Disable overwrite of PCI Access Control Services Control register in PCI root ports.

Attributes.WarningText: Source Validation changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: When set, the component validates the Bus Number from the Requester ID of upstream Requests against the secondary/subordinate Bus Numbers.

Attributes.WarningText: Translation Blocking changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: When set, the component blocks all upstream Memory Requests whose Address Translation (AT) field is not set to the default value.

Attributes.WarningText: P2P Request Redirect changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: This bit determines when the component redirects peer-to-peer Requests upstream.

Attributes.WarningText: P2P Completion Redirect changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Determines when the component redirects peer-to-peer Completions upstream, applicable only to Read Completions whose Relaxed Ordering Attribute is clear.

Attributes.WarningText: Upstream Forwarding Enable changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: When set, the component forwards upstream any Request or Completion TLPs it receives that were redirected upstream by a component lower in the hierarchy.

Attributes.WarningText: UPI Link Disable changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Disabling one of the CPU UPI links can save power. If maximum performance is desired, all UPI links should be left enabled. When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.  Note: The UPI function works only if 2 or more processors installed.

Attributes.WarningText: SNC changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: SNC (sub NUMA cluster) partitions the cores and last level cache into clusters with each cluster bound to a set of memory controllers in the system. SNC improves average latency to the last level cache.

Attributes.WarningText: Snoop Preference changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Select the appropriate snoop mode based on the workload. Setting the snoop mode preference does not always guarantee that it will be selected. The mode will be changed if the current hardware configuration does not support the desired mode. Also not that SNC has priority over the snoop mode.

Attributes.WarningText: XPT Prefetcher changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: XPT prefetch is a mechanism that enables a read request that is being sent to the last level cache to speculatively issue a copy of that read to the memory controller prefetching.

Attributes.WarningText: UPI Prefetcher changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: UPI prefetch is a mechanism to get the memory read started early on DDR bus. The UPI receive path will spawn a memory read to the memory controller prefetcher.  Note: The UPI function works only if 2 or more processors installed.

Attributes.WarningText: Total Memory Encryption changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable/Disable Total Memory Encryption (TME)

Attributes.WarningText: Multikey Total Memory Encryption changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable/Disable Multikey Total Memory Encryption (MK-TME)

Attributes.WarningText: SW Guard Extensions changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable/Disable Software Guard Extensions (SGX)

Attributes.WarningText: SGX Factory Reset changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Perform SGX Factory Reset, on subsequent boot: delete all registration data, if SGX enabled will force Initial Platform Establishment flow.

Attributes.WarningText: SGX Package Info In-Band Access changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable/Disable Software Guard Extensions (SGX) Package Info In-Band Access

Attributes.WarningText: PRMRR Size changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Setting the PRMRR Size

Attributes.WarningText: UMA-Based Clustering changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: UMA Based Clustering options include Disable (ALL2ALL), Hemisphere (2 cluster), and Quadrant (4 cluster, not supported on ICX). These option are only valid when SNC is disabled. If SNC is enabled, UMA-Based Clustering is automatically disabled by BIOS.

Attributes.WarningText: LLC Prefetch changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: F1 LLC prefetcher is an additional prefetch mechanism on top of the existing prefetchers that prefetch data into the core DCU and MLC. Enabling LLC prefetch gives the core prefetcher the ability to prefetch data directly into the LLC without necessarily filling into the MLC.

Attributes.WarningText: L2 RFO Prefetcher changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: One of 4 variables (IRQThreshold, StaleAtoS, CRQoSConfiguration, L2RFOPrefetchDisable) used to optimize performance for SAP HANA on servers with 2-hop memory configurations such as 4-socket ring, 6-socket and 8-socket configurations. Attributes.WarningText: UPI Link Frequency changes require a system reboot to take effect.

[Minimal Power] maximizes power savings. When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out. If user would like to change the settings, please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.  Note: The UPI function works only if 2 or more processors installed.

Attributes.WarningText: CPU Frequency Limits changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: The maximum frequency (turbo, AVX, and non turbo) can be restricted to a frequency that is between the maximum turbo frequency for the CPU installed and 1.2GHz. This can be useful for synchronizing CPU tasks. Note, the max frequency for N+1 cores cannot be higher than N cores. If an illegal frequency is entered, it will automatically be limited to a legal value. If the CPU frequency limits are being controlled through application software, leave this menu item at the default ([Full turbo uplift]), please choose [Custom Mode] in "Operating Mode" and [Enabled] in "Turbo Mode" located under "System Setting" submenu.

Attributes.WarningText: L1 changes require a system reboot to take effect.

Attributes.WarningText: ADDDC Sparing changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Enable/Disable ADDDC Sparing. Enabling ADDDC may cause reduced reliability of memory error correction in virtual lockstep under rare conditions.

Attributes.WarningText: Page Policy changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Adaptive Page Policy can improve performance for applications with a highly localized memory access pattern; Closed Page Policy can benefit applications that access memory more randomly.

Attributes.WarningText: 2x Refresh Rate changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: [Disabled] will set system with 1x refresh rate; [Auto] will set 2x refresh rate if system supports. Choose refresh rate 2x to mitigate rowhammer issue, this may have a performance side effect. When system has 16Gb 3DS with 4 Die DIMM, 2x refresh rate is not supported.

Attributes.WarningText: Mirror Mode changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Mirror Type configures the system hardware to shadow all memory writes to secondary memory. Full mirroring reduces the available system memory by half of the total installed memory. Partial mirroring reduces the available system memory by a maximum of 36 GB per processor.

Attributes.WarningText: Full Mirror changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Full mirroring reduces the available system memory by half of the total installed memory.

Attributes.WarningText: Partial Mirror changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Partial mirroring reduces the available system memory by percentage of up to 50% per processor. The percentage is set by "Partial Mirror Ratio In Basis Points".

Attributes.WarningText: Mirror Below 4GB changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.HelpText: Mirrors all available system memory below the 4GB address limit when enabled; typically 1 to 3 GB.

Attributes.WarningText: Partial Mirror Ratio In Basis Points changes require a system reboot to take effect.
Attributes.DisplayName: Partial Mirror Ratio In Basis Points
Attributes.HelpText: Configure the memory mirror ratio for the memory above 4 GB in basis points value. The valid range is 1 – 5000, meaning 0.01% to 50%. For example, to mirror 12.75% of memory, input the value 1275.

Attributes.HelpText: This option is a bit mask[19:0]: All 0 = disabled: bit-0=XMATS8, bit-1=XMATS16, bit-2=XMATS32, bit-3=XMATS64, bit-4=WCMATS8, bit-5=WCMCH8, bit-6=GNDB64, bit-7=MARCHCM64, bit-11=TWR, bit-12=DATARET, bit-13=MATS8TC1, bit-14=MATS8TC2, bit-15=MATS8TC3, bit-16=SKHYNIX, bit-17=SAMSUNG, bit-18=MICRON, bit-19=SCRAM_X2

When a preset mode is selected, the low-level settings are not changeable and will be grayed out.
